00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:32,150
♫ The love shall continue ♫

280
00:13:32,150 --> 00:13:34,440
Our leader is good indeed.
♫ The love shall continue ♫

281
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:35,330
He sees through their scheme

282
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,880
right away.

283
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,500
The scene where Qingwen tears up the fan.

284
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:42,950
I haven’t even started to tear anything.

285
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:45,540
Look how broken this fan is.

286
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,720
People are going to

287
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:48,820
make fun of my Qingwen

288
00:13:48,850 --> 00:13:50,450
if they saw this.

289
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,910
Mr. Shang,

290
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:54,170
I was being stupid.

291
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:55,980
You’re the bigger person.

292
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:57,560
You didn’t expose me

293
00:13:57,590 --> 00:13:59,440
in front of everyone.

294
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:00,380
I…

295
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:02,680
I’m ashamed.

296
00:14:03,350 --> 00:14:04,570
Mr. Wan and Mr. Liu are brothers

297
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,950
almost by blood.

298
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:07,880
Seeing how well I’m doing,

299
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,030
he’s worried that I’ll kick him out?

300
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:13,490
I’ll be frank.

301
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:16,050
I can’t do early rounds too often.

302
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:16,970
I’ll need a break soon.

303
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,850
I won’t be in Mr. Liu’s way.

304
00:14:19,330 --> 00:14:20,930
You can rest assured.

305
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:23,150
Stop messing around

306
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:24,440
for the next few days.

307
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,540
OK?

308
00:14:27,930 --> 00:14:29,580
Mr. Shang, you’re so generous.

309
00:14:30,180 --> 00:14:31,620
I… I am really ashamed.

310
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:32,240
I…

311
00:14:34,110 --> 00:14:35,170
Thank you.

312
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,450
I saw that he was

313
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,350
secretly talking there with Jiang Dengbao.

314
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:48,370
I wanted to warn you

315
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,880
but he hit me and I passed out.

316
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,810
He did it on purpose.

317
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:55,300
Really? Where did he hit you!

318
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:56,870
Here.

319
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,310
This son of a bitch.

320
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,490
But you didn’t get hurt for nothing.

321
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,710
Did you see my hand movement today

322
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:08,170
at the fan-tearing scene?

323
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:11,370
It was amazing.

324
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,730
See, a blessing in disguise.

325
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,980
I’ll keep doing that.

326
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:20,010
I was hit,

327
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,570
and you’re all happy here?

328
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,630
Leader!

329
00:15:22,770 --> 00:15:23,560
Leader.

330
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,450
Please come.

331
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,740
The landlord is here.

332
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:28,550
We have to leave if we can’t pay the rent.

333
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,300
I mean, leader…

334
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,050
Can you say something?

335
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,760
What are we going to do?

336
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:44,560
I only care about singing.

337
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:46,980
Why are you asking for money from me now?

338
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:47,830
Why don’t we have enough

339
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:49,220
all of a sudden?

340
00:15:50,370 --> 00:15:51,840
You don’t say.

341
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:53,490
After our accountant resigned

342
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:54,980
and went home,

343
00:15:55,010 --> 00:15:57,350
you couldn’t bother to hire another.

344
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:58,070
That’s fine.

345
00:15:58,280 --> 00:16:00,250
But you need to take care of the money.

346
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,130
Our guys

347
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:02,810
are always taking money

348
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:04,540
from our account.

349
00:16:04,950 --> 00:16:05,650
Today could be

350
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,920
someone feeling sick.

351
00:16:06,950 --> 00:16:08,080
Tomorrow could be

352
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,490
someone’s grandma passed away.

353
00:16:09,980 --> 00:16:10,820
I’ll say

354
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:12,290
they’re all lying to get the money.

355
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:12,920
Don’t be silly.

356
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:14,810
Who would claim their grandma to be dead

357
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:15,930
just to get that money?

358
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,770
Well, lie or not,

359
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,100
you’ll find out eventually.

360
00:16:22,890 --> 00:16:23,890
Everything aside.

361
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,130
Your priority is

362
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,530
to get the landlord out of here.

363
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,370
No way.

364
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:27,970
I can’t talk to

365
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,130
someone

366
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:30,320
as rude as him.

367
00:16:30,350 --> 00:16:31,300
I’ll try to punch him.

368
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,330
I’ll beat him up

369
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:33,150
before I even start the conversation.

370
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:34,200
We’ll all be kicked out by the end of today.

371
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:34,980
Well…

372
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:42,580
It’s already so late…

373
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,280
Shall we take the money our previous leader left…

374
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:44,890
No way!

375
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,400
That’s our last straw.

376
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:48,410
We have to save it.

377
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:52,660
What do you want to do then?

378
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:58,930
I’ll find some money.

379
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,370
Give this to him. Make him wait a bit.

380
00:17:01,150 --> 00:17:01,900
I can’t do this.

381
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:04,160
You’ve been wearing this since you were a baby.

382
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,609
It could be

383
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:06,450
from your birth parents.

384
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,200
You can’t give him this.

385
00:17:07,230 --> 00:17:09,050
This is pointless.

386
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:09,810
Focus on what matters the most

387
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:10,900
at this moment.

388
00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:11,530
Make sure Shijiu

389
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:12,690
doesn’t do anything crazy.

390
00:17:12,910 --> 00:17:14,089
Can’t have them hurt

391
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:15,300
a girl like her.

392
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,089
Go ahead.

393
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:39,530
What?

394
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,730
Don’t you know what

395
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:43,730
I’m capable of here?

396
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,690
What are you doing here, in broad daylight?

397
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:48,690
Kid,

398
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:50,930
let me make it clear.

399
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:55,090
This is the contract that you signed.

400
00:17:55,220 --> 00:17:55,480
♫ How great that you tore the fan ♫

401
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,330
Signatures, fingerprints. All here.
♫ How great that you tore the fan ♫

402
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,940
This is all legal.

403
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,640
Even if we bring this to the police,

404
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:03,200
I will win.

405
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:04,630
Shall we?

406
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,310
Ba Ye, what are you doing?

407
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:10,660
Look,

408
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,370
I have some jewellery with me.

409
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,470
It’s worth something.

410
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,130
Shijiu, Ronglan, everyone.

411
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,360
We can all put something together.

412
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:19,880
Where do I find anything to give?

413
00:18:19,910 --> 00:18:21,610
I only have my costumes.

414
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:23,250
I won’t be able to perform without them.

415
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,600
Dasheng?

416
00:18:25,630 --> 00:18:26,630
Don’t look at me.

417
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,400
Men can’t save anything.

418
00:18:28,430 --> 00:18:29,010
A trip to the brothel,

419
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,300
I come out in debt.

420
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:34,210
We’re all penniless.

421
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:36,440
Wait a second.

422
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,160
Doesn’t Liuyue have something?

423
00:18:38,190 --> 00:18:39,130
Shuiyun Theatre is struggling,

424
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,340
help us out.

425
00:18:43,180 --> 00:18:45,010
I… I can’t do this…

426
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:45,540
What?

427
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,200
You actually have the money.

428
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:51,160
Then I don’t have to wait.

429
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,310
Little girl,

430
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,770
do you want to give it to me?

431
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,690
Or do you want me to take it from you?

432
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:58,220
No…

433
00:18:59,000 --> 00:18:59,580
Hey…

434
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:00,740
Ba Ye.

435
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:01,990
Don’t you dare touch her.

436
00:19:02,180 --> 00:19:02,950
What’s happening here?

437
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,520
Are we starting a fight?

438
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:05,100
I…

439
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:06,240
Don’t do this.

440
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:07,190
What are you doing?

441
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,130
What’s going on here?

442
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,420
Starting a fight scene without me?

443
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,680
What’s the next verse after

444
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,470
“A shout facing toward Xiliang”?

445
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:23,590
I’ve seen this play.

446
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:27,020
You’re saying I’m the bandit here?

447
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,580
Fine.

448
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,150
Take a look here.

449
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:35,460
Who’s not paying the rent? Who is the bandit?

450
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:37,640
Just 600 kuai.

451
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:39,730
Why are you even being so mad at a little girl?

452
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:42,260
I want every penny of it. 600.

453
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:43,550
Here is 600.

454
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:44,980
All here.

455
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:50,890
That’s so much…

456
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,160
Where did he get this?

457
00:19:52,190 --> 00:19:53,830
If the amount is correct, kindly show yourself out.

458
00:19:54,090 --> 00:19:55,350
We’ll talk next year.

459
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,680
I don’t think we’re seeing each other again.

460
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,100
Mr. Shang,

461
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,190
I’ll give you a notice now.

462
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:07,580
This place,

463
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:09,700
we won’t be renting it to you next year.

464
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:12,290
We signed a 3 year contract.

465
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:13,960
What are you doing?

466
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:16,810
Look at your staff.

467
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,020
These brats.

468
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,740
Look what they’ve done

469
00:20:19,770 --> 00:20:21,200
to the walls

470
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:22,420
and the floor tiles.

471
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:25,120
You’re lucky that I’m not asking for more to fix it.

472
00:20:25,150 --> 00:20:26,280
Don’t mess with me.

473
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:28,410
Tell me exactly why.

474
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,350
Mr. Shang.

475
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,070
We thought having someone so popular here

476
00:20:33,420 --> 00:20:35,500
would be a good thing.

477
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:36,620
Thought it’d make us look better.

478
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:38,690
But who knew

479
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:40,820
you would offend Commander Cao.

480
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:43,940
What if he came back here one day?

481
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:45,290
What if he just took his gun out?

482
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:46,090
Bang.

483
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,750
This would be a crime scene.

484
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:48,970
We’ve been having

485
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:49,890
bad luck

486
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,250
since we moved in here.

487
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,010
I’ll say

488
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:52,690
the Fengshui here is already horrible.

489
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,050
Is this already a crime thing?

490
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,450
You little brat.

491
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:56,150
Say that again?

492
00:20:56,180 --> 00:20:57,030
We will leave next year!

493
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,810
Ba Ye. We’ll see you around.

494
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,670
Find yourself a new place now.

495
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,410
Huh. He’s no more than a relative

496
00:21:22,420 --> 00:21:23,510
of the police station director.

497
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:24,170
Who does he think he is?

498
00:21:24,180 --> 00:21:25,550
An overlord?

499
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:27,550
We have a dozen of us

500
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:29,190
to feed every day.

501
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:30,630
If we couldn’t

502
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,350
find a place to perform,

503
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,430
we can’t get through this

504
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:36,790
even if we sold ourselves.

505
00:21:37,010 --> 00:21:38,150
If you don’t want to stay, feel free to leave now.

506
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:39,270
No one is making you stay.

507
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,550
Let’s see who leaves first.

508
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:42,710
What does that mean?

509
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:43,430
What are you saying?

510
00:21:43,440 --> 00:21:44,470
No one leaves. I’ll go.

511
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:47,510
Leader! Leader! Hey!

512
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:49,750
Leave now. Go ahead.

513
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:50,630
You don’t like it here. Go away.

514
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:51,110
Go. Go now.

515
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,190
Stop it! Stop fighting.

516
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,870
Can’t you see?

517
00:21:54,430 --> 00:21:55,870
He gave away his costume

518
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:58,070
to get the 600.

519
00:21:58,320 --> 00:22:00,470
All you do is fight!

520
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:02,830
Costume?

521
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,630
We’re pawning our costumes now?

522
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:08,750
What’s happening?

523
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,590
Commander Cao

524
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:12,310
is going to ruin our lives.

525
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,070
Mr. Cheng…

526
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:40,230
Why is this car here in the middle?

527
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,430
Mr. Cheng.

528
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:46,710
Weren’t you at home resting?

529
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:47,590
I…

530
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:48,990
I was just thinking

531
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,350
who can afford

532
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:51,510
this brand new American car

533
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:52,510
across the Peking city.

534
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:53,710
Who knew?

535
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:54,910
It’s you.

536
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:56,670
Adjutant Sun.

537
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:01,430
Something with the cargo place.

538
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,270
They asked to see the boss.

539
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:05,390
I have to come.

540
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:09,910
When you get better, Mr. Cheng,

541
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,150
Commander Cao wants to see you.

542
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,990
I don’t think I have the time to leave town.

543
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:19,630
Adjutant Sun, you don’t know.

544
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,700
Last night,

545
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,410
we had a thief in our cargo shop.

546
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:25,390
From Laozi mountain.

547
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,790
And told them about

548
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,390
my shipment.

549
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,070
Things are complicated for me now.

550
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:34,350
But this guy

551
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,310
doesn’t really look like a gangster.

552
00:23:37,190 --> 00:23:38,740
More like a bandit who’s a soldier.

553
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,110
Well, still a bandit. Right?

554
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,390
Mr. Cheng. You’re very funny.

555
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:49,630
You are a lucky person.

556
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:50,750
You are blessed.

557
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,440
No bandit can harm you.

558
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,260
Adjutant Sun, you always know what to say.

559
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:05,390
Look.

560
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:07,950
Please tell Mr. Cao,

561
00:24:09,060 --> 00:24:10,030
don’t park his car in front of my house

562
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:12,040
in the future.

563
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:13,910
It makes it very inconvenient for me

564
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,070
to go in and out.

565
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:17,110
We’re a family.

566
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:19,990
Would be bad if we run into each other.

567
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:20,670
Right.

568
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,030
I will make sure to give him the message.

569
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:22,990
Well then.

570
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:24,950
Could you move a bit?

571
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:24,590
What are you doing?

572
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:30,750
You.

573
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,070
It’s me.

574
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:34,430
We’ve met before.

575
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:35,430
Earlier this month.

576
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:36,430
At Huibin Theatre.

577
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:47,510
What are you doing here?

578
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,150
How did you get in here?

579
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:50,030
I…

580
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,030
I’m here for Commander Cao.

581
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:54,390
From the front door.

582
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,030
Commander Cao does not live here.

583
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:02,460
This is my brother’s place.

584
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,510
He doesn’t live here?

585
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,030
He doesn’t live with his wife?

586
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,750
He lives at the military camp outside of the town.

587
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:16,630
What do you want?

588
00:26:18,450 --> 00:26:19,790
Something bad happened at Shuiyun Theatre.

589
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:20,990
All because of him.

590
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:31,630
What do you want to do to him with this?

591
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,670
Did you plan to kill him?

592
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:43,110
He has soldiers with guns surrounding him.

593
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:44,790
Aren’t you afraid?

594
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:48,190
His life’s worth more than mine.

595
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,390
One for one.

596
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:50,270
I’m not afraid.

597
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:52,790
Do you know that everything happened

598
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:53,870
because of him?

599
00:26:54,060 --> 00:26:55,110
If it wasn’t because of him,

600
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,710
they would still let us perform.

601
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:57,710
As long as we get to perform,

602
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,230
our leader will not starve.

603
00:26:59,440 --> 00:27:00,830
Even my sister was bullied.

604
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:02,310
Do you know

605
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:03,190
because of him

606
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:05,110
we’re all going to starve soon?

607
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:06,870
As a man,

608
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:08,190
I have to do something.

609
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:13,990
That’s it?

610
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,590
Then stop performing.

611
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,590
Do something else.

612
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:24,990
Work for the government.

613
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:26,710
My brother always says

614
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:29,990
brute courage can’t last.

615
00:27:30,270 --> 00:27:32,750
Long-term stability will come

616
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:35,630
when you become someone important one day.

617
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:37,510
Understood?

618
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:39,630
I…

619
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:41,190
I…

620
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,270
Xiaozhang!

621
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,190
Lunch is ready.

622
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:51,070
You haven’t eaten yet?

623
00:27:51,290 --> 00:27:52,150
Eat what?

624
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,150
The pan?

625
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:01,310
Remember what I told you just now?

626
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:07,710
Go have some food.

627
00:28:11,310 --> 00:28:12,390
I will give it back to you.

628
00:28:23,780 --> 00:28:26,550
I’m here to apologise to lady Ping.

629
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:30,350
What are you talking about?

630
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:33,830
I’m very sorry.

631
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,390
I didn’t stop Shang Xirui

632
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:37,830
that day.

633
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:41,550
Even his father,

634
00:28:41,740 --> 00:28:42,630
his brother,

635
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:44,430
even Mengping.

636
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:47,110
No one can stop him.

637
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,190
Let alone you.

638
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:52,270
I’d lectured him before.

639
00:28:52,870 --> 00:28:54,230
Who knew? This silly kid.

640
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:57,190
He doesn’t care about any relationship.

641
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,590
He said you lied to him.

642
00:28:59,780 --> 00:29:00,600
Said he hated you guys.

643
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,210
He hated you so much.

644
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:05,530
Silly boy.

645
00:29:06,520 --> 00:29:09,390
He’s always so stubborn.

646
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:12,870
I didn’t mean to lie to him.

647
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:14,550
I told him

648
00:29:15,620 --> 00:29:17,310
that he was the most important person to me.

649
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,920
I really consider him my own brother.

650
00:29:24,020 --> 00:29:25,230
I didn’t want him to be upset.

651
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:27,250
I even tried to break up with Zhixin.

652
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:30,940
But who can control your feelings

653
00:29:31,090 --> 00:29:33,500
when it comes to love?

654
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:36,630
At the end,

655
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,920
I couldn’t help.

656
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:46,470
Shang Xirui cared about you very much.

657
00:29:47,220 --> 00:29:49,050
He couldn’t get over

658
00:29:49,510 --> 00:29:51,000
the fact that you left.

659
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:53,110
He was sold to Shuiyun Theatre as a kid.

660
00:29:54,230 --> 00:29:56,390
Mengping raised him.

661
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,130
He loves her.

662
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:02,230
Like a child loving a mother.

663
00:30:04,710 --> 00:30:05,910
But this love…

664
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:08,660
It gets too heavy. Too harsh.

665
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:10,280
And it’s not right anymore.

666
00:30:11,940 --> 00:30:15,390
He can’t stand her caring about anyone else more than him.

667
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:18,430
I remember

668
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:20,630
the first time he saw me and Mengping together.

669
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:23,580
He looked like

670
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,590
he was going to eat us alive.

671
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:30,430
He ran to me and started to shout at me.

672
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:33,520
What kind of brother is this?

673
00:30:33,890 --> 00:30:35,340
He’s a maniac.

674
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:39,020
She promised that

675
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:43,150
I’m the most important person for her.

676
00:30:43,830 --> 00:30:46,190
We’re family without being related.

677
00:30:46,790 --> 00:30:49,330
Our relationship goes beyond any other relationships.

678
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:51,380
He wouldn’t let Mengping be with me.

679
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:54,750
If anyone asks

680
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:58,440
“You don’t want your sister to be with anyone.

681
00:30:59,330 --> 00:31:01,030
Then are you going to marry her?”

682
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:03,190
Guess what he said?

683
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:05,550
What did he say?

684
00:31:05,620 --> 00:31:06,380
He said:

685
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:08,430
“I don’t want to be her husband.

686
00:31:09,140 --> 00:31:10,710
What does she need a husband for?”

687
00:31:11,410 --> 00:31:13,200
What’s there that a husband can do

688
00:31:13,210 --> 00:31:14,440
while he can’t?

689
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,350
Anything Mengping wants,

690
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:17,750
he’ll do it.

691
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:20,030
Look at what he said.

692
00:31:20,850 --> 00:31:22,430
It’s beyond childish.

693
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:23,980
It’s stupid.

694
00:31:28,890 --> 00:31:30,190
I guess, most of these geniuses

695
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:32,230
are better than everyone else

696
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:34,800
in a certain field.

697
00:31:35,130 --> 00:31:37,870
But they also lack other things.

698
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:40,770
Maybe they’re physically disabled.

699
00:31:41,280 --> 00:31:42,830
Maybe they have a funny temperament.

700
00:31:43,410 --> 00:31:45,220
Maybe they’ve been through a lot of hardship.

701
00:31:45,380 --> 00:31:46,510
Maybe their family is broken.

702
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:47,760
Maybe they die at a young age.

703
00:31:48,830 --> 00:31:51,660
Shang Xirui has great talent when it comes to opera.

704
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:53,030
We all see that.

705
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:56,550
Expecting him to be good at socialising

706
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:57,510
and good at people,

707
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,430
seems to be a bit much.

708
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,190
God is fair.

709
00:32:02,110 --> 00:32:03,510
He was given the talent for singing.

710
00:32:03,810 --> 00:32:05,390
But left without social skills.

711
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:06,300
Brother,

712
00:32:07,500 --> 00:32:09,250
are you trying to defend him?

713
00:32:10,540 --> 00:32:11,450
Nonsense.

714
00:32:16,700 --> 00:32:18,330
I was also extremely mad at him.

715
00:32:19,860 --> 00:32:21,520
But he explained it to me that way.

716
00:32:21,820 --> 00:32:23,090
I came to accept it.

717
00:32:24,340 --> 00:32:27,830
He was born this way.

718
00:32:29,260 --> 00:32:32,070
The more people ask him about this, the more confused he is.

719
00:32:33,220 --> 00:32:35,780
He even came to me and Mengping,

720
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:39,210
saying that indeed we had to get married,

721
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:42,820
and that he’d allow it

722
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:46,560
but Mengping has to put him first

723
00:32:46,860 --> 00:32:48,040
and she could never put me first.

724
00:32:48,890 --> 00:32:50,570
I’d simply someone who sleeps next to her

725
00:32:50,580 --> 00:32:52,410
someone who has a baby with her.

726
00:32:54,340 --> 00:32:56,050
He said that to me.

727
00:32:56,540 --> 00:32:58,330
What did he expect Mengping to say?

728
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:03,410
We couldn’t come to an agreement because of that.

729
00:33:04,370 --> 00:33:07,450
You know what happened afterwards.

730
00:33:08,460 --> 00:33:09,600
It’s funny.

731
00:33:10,660 --> 00:33:13,410
Because the Shang Xirui that I know is different every day.

732
00:33:14,710 --> 00:33:17,040
He has such a strong connection with Mengping.

733
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:18,650
It’s very touching.

734
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,190
To be honest,

735
00:33:24,060 --> 00:33:25,400
if he wasn’t like this,

736
00:33:25,590 --> 00:33:26,530
crazy and stubborn,

737
00:33:27,300 --> 00:33:28,850
I’d appreciate him.

738
00:33:30,260 --> 00:33:31,790
He is

739
00:33:33,180 --> 00:33:34,240
indeed

740
00:33:37,380 --> 00:33:38,700
a very strange

741
00:33:39,190 --> 00:33:41,050
and very peculiar person.

742
00:33:42,740 --> 00:33:44,130
Here at Peking,

743
00:33:45,780 --> 00:33:47,690
if he continues to do what he does,

744
00:33:49,010 --> 00:33:51,130
no one can tolerate him forever.

745
00:33:52,260 --> 00:33:53,400
What is he going to do then?

746
00:33:57,450 --> 00:34:00,280
This special relationship between you two

747
00:34:00,900 --> 00:34:02,460
is once-in-a-life-time.

748
00:34:03,210 --> 00:34:04,300
You won’t see it anywhere else.

749
00:34:13,340 --> 00:34:16,050
Bingtanghulu!

750
00:34:25,020 --> 00:34:26,170
You’re still sick.

751
00:34:26,290 --> 00:34:28,130
Shall I take you back first?

752
00:34:28,610 --> 00:34:29,290
No.

753
00:34:30,260 --> 00:34:32,139
I have to see Mr. Shang.

754
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:35,170
The journalist was saying a lot of things about him.

755
00:34:35,300 --> 00:34:36,929
I need to know how he is.

756
00:34:38,139 --> 00:34:38,770
Mr. Cheng,

757
00:34:40,219 --> 00:34:42,940
you’re being very generous already.

758
00:34:43,420 --> 00:34:44,679
He’s the one who needs to work harder.

759
00:34:45,409 --> 00:34:46,199
What’s more,

760
00:34:46,699 --> 00:34:48,650
your relationship with him isn’t that strong.

761
00:34:49,300 --> 00:34:50,110
Should we just let it be?

762
00:34:51,940 --> 00:34:53,250
What do you mean not strong?

763
00:34:54,380 --> 00:34:55,290
Mr. Shang’s got all his costumes

764
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:57,170
from our place.

765
00:34:57,670 --> 00:34:59,210
We made some money because of him.

766
00:34:59,820 --> 00:35:02,010
We can’t just let him go through all of this alone.

767
00:35:03,500 --> 00:35:05,200
Across the Peking city,

768
00:35:05,750 --> 00:35:08,150
no one can run their business better than you.

769
00:35:09,940 --> 00:35:10,570
Alright then.

770
00:35:10,740 --> 00:35:12,290
Let’s go to Shuiyun Theatre.

771
00:35:12,540 --> 00:35:13,090
No.

772
00:35:14,140 --> 00:35:14,890
Huibin Theatre.

773
00:35:16,540 --> 00:35:16,960
Today

774
00:35:16,980 --> 00:35:19,010
is his last day performing there.

775
00:35:20,980 --> 00:35:21,850
Mr. Shang. You’re here.

776
00:35:22,180 --> 00:35:23,210
There’s hot water on the stove.

777
00:35:23,340 --> 00:35:24,290
Let me get you some warm water.

778
00:35:24,540 --> 00:35:24,890
Thank you.

779
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:25,410
You’re more than welcome.

780
00:35:26,380 --> 00:35:26,890
Mr. Shang.

781
00:35:28,620 --> 00:35:29,250
Xiao Lai.

782
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:30,730
Go help with others.

783
00:35:31,220 --> 00:35:33,130
I’ll help Mr. Shang with his hair.

784
00:35:34,540 --> 00:35:35,510
No rush.

785
00:35:35,640 --> 00:35:37,280
He’ll have a headache if you do it too soon.

786
00:35:37,460 --> 00:35:37,970
Got it.

787
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:40,010
Just let me know when he’s ready.

788
00:35:40,140 --> 00:35:40,570
Sure.

789
00:35:40,620 --> 00:35:41,250
Thank you.

790
00:35:48,860 --> 00:35:49,530
Mr. Shang.

791
00:35:50,900 --> 00:35:52,170
You’re here early today.

792
00:35:56,700 --> 00:35:58,130
Well it’s your last play here.

793
00:35:58,460 --> 00:36:00,050
Got to be prepared.

794
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:01,970
You’re pretty early as well.

795
00:36:03,540 --> 00:36:04,570
We’re different.

796
00:36:05,220 --> 00:36:07,270
Longchun Troupe has more people. More performers.

797
00:36:07,290 --> 00:36:09,130
It takes us longer to get ready.

798
00:36:11,110 --> 00:36:12,370
Speaking of that,

799
00:36:13,340 --> 00:36:16,010
we use this makeup room now.

800
00:36:16,060 --> 00:36:17,860
Do you mind doing your makeup outside?

801
00:36:18,340 --> 00:36:19,510
As long as I’m going on that stage,

802
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:21,880
I should have my room here.

803
00:36:22,420 --> 00:36:23,500
Even in the Palace of Eternal Life,

804
00:36:23,740 --> 00:36:26,690
Lady Yang died next to the emperor.

805
00:36:27,580 --> 00:36:30,170
You keep pushing the limit.

806
00:36:31,100 --> 00:36:31,810
Are you upset about something?

807
00:36:32,820 --> 00:36:33,690
Suck it up.

808
00:36:34,350 --> 00:36:36,060
What if I can’t?

809
00:36:40,540 --> 00:36:42,290
What’s with all this fuss?

810
00:36:42,540 --> 00:36:43,090
Mr. Cheng.

811
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:45,330
Mr. Cheng.

812
00:36:45,460 --> 00:36:46,410
What brought you here?

813
00:36:47,620 --> 00:36:48,820
I’m here to see you.

814
00:36:53,740 --> 00:36:56,570
What’s this sour smell here?

815
00:36:56,580 --> 00:36:58,290
It stinks.

816
00:36:59,860 --> 00:37:00,490
Mr. Shang.

817
00:37:01,060 --> 00:37:03,850
Why don’t you come to my balcony to do your makeup?

818
00:37:04,020 --> 00:37:05,050
It’s more spacious.

819
00:37:05,210 --> 00:37:07,290
We can also enjoy the play for a bit.

820
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:12,440
Gentlemen,

821
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:15,930
- thanks for your hard work. - Thank you sir.

822
00:37:16,620 --> 00:37:17,130
Thank you, Mr. Cheng.

823
00:37:17,300 --> 00:37:18,410
Help us tidy up a bit.

824
00:37:18,420 --> 00:37:19,130
Thank you, Mr. Cheng.

825
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:20,370
Thank you, Mr. Cheng.

826
00:37:21,140 --> 00:37:21,890
Mr. Shang,

827
00:37:22,540 --> 00:37:23,130
let’s go.

828
00:37:35,020 --> 00:37:36,690
You’ve got some fans. Big deal…

829
00:37:37,980 --> 00:37:39,890
I’ll take your seat then.

830
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:51,970
Thank you. You can take a break now.

831
00:37:52,700 --> 00:37:53,130
Okay.

832
00:37:53,460 --> 00:37:54,720
Don’t forget to go back to the backstage.

833
00:37:54,740 --> 00:37:55,880
You need to get changed.

834
00:37:57,900 --> 00:37:59,680
I didn’t have the time to say hi to you just now.

835
00:37:59,940 --> 00:38:01,290
You came with us anyway.

836
00:38:02,140 --> 00:38:03,610
Such an honour.

837
00:38:04,220 --> 00:38:04,770
Thank you very much.

838
00:38:06,180 --> 00:38:08,010
Mr. Cheng, you’re very kind. My pleasure.

839
00:38:08,700 --> 00:38:10,060
Jiang Dengbao doesn’t have any manner.

840
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:11,090
He thinks he’s the best.

841
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:12,330
I don’t even care to work for him.

842
00:38:12,740 --> 00:38:14,520
Mr. Shang has always been very kind.

843
00:38:15,020 --> 00:38:15,630
Mr. Shang,

844
00:38:15,690 --> 00:38:17,230
don’t hesitate to let me know if you need help with anything.

845
